# Optimize Portfolio (Hedge Fund) Page

The [PortfolioPage](file:///c:/Users/PC/Desktop/quant/smarkquant-v.5.1/frontend/src/app/portfolio/page.tsx#140-1298) contains a background interval that updates numbers (`equity`, `dayPnl`, and `lastUpdate`) continuously when active bots are running (every 1.8 seconds). This triggers a full re-render of the component.
During each re-render, the page recalculates expensive metrics by iterating and sorting arrays (`sessions`, `transactions`, etc.), which can lead to UI lag, battery drain, and poor performance, especially when there are many sessions.

## Proposed Changes

We will use React's `useMemo` to cache all computationally expensive derived variables. Thus, they will only be re-evaluated when the actual raw data (e.g., `sessions`, `transactions`) changes, rather than on every ticker heartbeat.

### c:\Users\PC\Desktop\quant\smarkquant-v.5.1\frontend\src\app\portfolio\page.tsx

Implementation of `useMemo` to optimize expensive calculations:

- **Derived Metrics**: Wrap `backtests`, `liveSessions`, totals (PnL, trades, fees, wins, etc.), ratios, and `avgExpectancy` inside a `useMemo`.
- **Strategy Breakdown**: Wrap `stratMap` population and sorting into a `useMemo`.
- **Equity Curves & Downsampling**: Wrap the `sampledCurve` downsampling process.
- **Combined Fund-flow Curve (`cumCurve`)**: Wrap the sorting and merging of `completedTxEvents` and `sessionEvents` into a `cumCurve`.
- **Drawdown and Allocations**: Wrap `ddChart`, `allocData`, and `recentSessions` in `useMemo`.

These changes will memoize computations natively, substantially reducing the amount of JavaScript execution every 1.8s.

